* def_family_regression.dts
* Runtime DEF-family testbed — DEFCMD / DEFFN / EXAMPLE (RUNTIME_DEF_FAMILY lane).
*
* Proves runtime definition, invocation, argument passthrough, expression resolution,
* composition with a builtin, listing, and removal — all session-only, with no rebuild.
* Kept as the PERMANENT worked example of the AI-friendly dev-tools.
*
* Environment bootstrap (regression doctrine: every test sets its own environment):
* sets ECHO OFF + STOP_ON_ERROR OFF so the intentional post-removal "unknown" lines do
* not abort the run. This test opens/mutates NO table and NO file — only the session
* command/function registries, which it cleans up (UNDEFCMD/UNDEFFN). Safe for the
* default suite once proven green.
*
* Expected (grep the transcript between BEGIN/END):
*   EXAMPLE_TEST_expect_OK:              -> OK
*   DEFCMD_invoke_expect_DEFCMD_BODY_OK: -> DEFCMD_BODY_OK
*   DEFCMD_args_...:                     -> DEFCMD_BODY_OK a b
*   DEFCMD_removed_...:                  -> Unknown command: PINGCMD
*   DEFFN_resolve_expect_hello:          -> hello
*   DEFFN_compose_expect_HELLO:          -> HELLO
*   DEFFN_removed_expect_error:          -> (function evaluation failed)
*
* Run:  REGRESSION RUN DEF_FAMILY
*   or: DOTSCRIPT dottalkpp/data/scripts/dotscript/def_family_regression.dts

SET ECHO OFF
STOP_ON_ERROR OFF

FORMULA "DEF-FAMILY-REGRESSION-BEGIN"

* --- EXAMPLE reference built-in (token routing / smallest command) ---
FORMULA "EXAMPLE_TEST_expect_OK:"
EXAMPLE TEST

* --- DEFCMD: define -> invoke -> arg passthrough -> list -> remove -> gone ---
DEFCMD PINGCMD = DEFCMD_BODY_OK
FORMULA "DEFCMD_invoke_expect_DEFCMD_BODY_OK:"
PINGCMD
FORMULA "DEFCMD_args_expect_DEFCMD_BODY_OK_a_b:"
PINGCMD a b
DEFCMD LIST
UNDEFCMD PINGCMD
FORMULA "DEFCMD_removed_expect_Unknown_PINGCMD:"
PINGCMD

* --- DEFFN: define -> resolve in expression -> compose with builtin -> list -> remove ---
DEFFN GREETFN = hello
FORMULA "DEFFN_resolve_expect_hello:"
? GREETFN()
FORMULA "DEFFN_compose_expect_HELLO:"
? UPPER(GREETFN())
DEFFN LIST
UNDEFFN GREETFN
FORMULA "DEFFN_removed_expect_error:"
? GREETFN()

FORMULA "DEF-FAMILY-REGRESSION-END"
